{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Germans were well aware that nobody was going to take the Jews, and nobody was going to help the Jews unless it was on an exchange basis.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was some reason why the British people would take these Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the only reason why the Brits would take Jews would be because they were British.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in the same way, Ecuador and Venezuela-- if there were Jews who had official visas to enter Venezuela and Ecuador, then these countries might take those Jews.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Many people say that these visas were actually forged and all that, and that they would never have got in anyway.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I don't think any of them were ever exchanged, but that was the idea.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so all those people had blue stamps in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were eventually moved around from the barracks that we were in originally in Westerbork to other barracks, where all these people with blue stamps seem to have been congregated.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because we were held back in Westerbork, like in Amsterdam where we were not rounded up for a long time because my father worked for the [INAUDIBLE], and maybe also because of our British connection/ the same happened again in Westerbork.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We stayed in Westerbork from the [? 20th ?] of June, 1943 until the [? 1st ?] of February, 1944.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we stayed in Westerbork for a very, very long time because, basically, it was a transit camp, and most people didn't stay in Westerbork more than a week.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was lots of good things about Westerbork, but the bad thing about Westerbork was that every Monday afternoon, there would be a train of cattle trucks-- of about 20 cattle trucks.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Would roll into the middle of Westerbork camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
